author: dkulp
msg: [CXF-3365] Updates to allow considering the incoming policy alternative
Relativise returned claim names against the namespace
Updates to add a <cxf:workqueue> element to the core schema to make it
easier to configure the workqueue parameters.
Delay the creation of the actual threadpool till first call to execute
to allow configuration ahead of time.

author: robbie
msg: QPID-3525: stop the client from accidentally consuming the messages it is actually trying to recover when using 0-8/9/9-1. Also stops it acking the message from the in-progress onMessage delivery after Session.recover() was called.
Applied patch from Oleksandr Rudyy<orudyy@gmail.com> and myself.

author: robbie
msg: QPID-3527: update handling of auto-ack messages for 0-10 to send acks (asynchronously) on a per-message basis rather than batching for 1 second, update handling for other ack modes to be clearer with respect to 0-8/0-10 behavioural differences. Remove some redundant methods from AMQSession, updating handling of 'no consume'/'isBrowseOnly' such that BasicMessageConsumer is always supplied a single consistent answer for whether it is non-consuming or not.
Applied patch from Oleksandr Rudyy<orudyy@gmail.com> and myself.
